  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the top portions of two circular arcs. The left ends are approximately parallel, but the space between them increases toward the right. The space between the arcs is labeled Soapy Water Layer. The spaces outside the arcs are labeled Air. Point P is indicated on the upper circular arc near the left end, and Point Q is indicated on the upper circular arc near the right end. An arrow labeled Normally Incident Light, where wavelength equals lambda sub 0, points to each of P and Q. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"/images/3b6102f8707a1aa0c0c4228ac7008caa.svg\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A soap bubble consists of an approximately spherical shape made from a thin layer of soapy water, with air on each side of the thin layer, as shown in the figure. For light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> that is normally incident at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, the soapy water layer is the minimum thickness <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub min\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"t sub min\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mi>min</mi></msub></math></span></span> needed for there to be maximum constructive interference of the light reflected from the two water-air interfaces. At point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span>, the soapy water layer has a different thickness, but there is still maximum constructive interference of the reflections from the two interfaces when light of the same wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is normally incident on the bubble. Which of the following could be the smallest possible thickness of the layer at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
